      "module_path": "tddd::catalogue_v2::traits",
      "docs": "Identity-only trait implementation record. Modified in this track to add: (1) impl_generics (MethodGenericParam array, type params only) and impl_where_predicates (WherePredicateDecl array) per ADR D2/IN-06; (2) for_ (Option<String>, serde default None) per ADR D4/IN-13. for_ carries a fully-qualified self-type path (e.g. domain::tddd::new_typegraph_codec_error::NewTypeGraphCodecError) when the implementing type is external to the catalogue's crate. When None (the common case), the A-codec derives the for_ type from the parent TypeEntry context. This enables cross-crate impl declarations such as impl From<CatalogueToExtendedCrateCodecError> for NewTypeGraphCodecError to be represented in the catalogue and evaluated by the signal evaluator.",
